how ?
Queue<TreeNode> queue = new LinkedList<>();

Then this is possible too
Queue<TreeNode> queue = new ArrayList<>();

Queue<TreeNode> queue = new LinkedList<>();
тЬФ Why it works:
Queue is an interface
LinkedList implements Queue

So Java allows:
ЁЯСЙ interface reference тЖТ implementation object

тЭМ This is INVALID
Queue<TreeNode> queue = new ArrayList<>();
тЭМ Why it fails:
ArrayList does NOT implement Queue

It only implements:
    List
    Collection

So Java will give:
Type mismatch: cannot convert from ArrayList to Queue



ЁЯЯв 1. LinkedList
Queue<TreeNode> q = new LinkedList<>();
тЬФ Features:
    Doubly-linked list
    Allows null (not recommended)
Implements Queue + Deque
тЪая╕П Downsides:
    More memory overhead
    Slower than ArrayDeque in most cases


ЁЯЯв 2. ArrayDeque тнР (Best general choice)
Queue<TreeNode> q = new ArrayDeque<>();
тЬФ Features:
    Resizable array
    Faster than LinkedList
No null elements allowed
ЁЯЪА Why preferred:
    Better cache performance
    No node allocation overhead

ЁЯСЙ Use this by default unless you need something special


ЁЯЯб 3. PriorityQueue (Not FIFO!)
Queue<Integer> q = new PriorityQueue<>();
тЬФ Features:
    Orders elements by priority (min-heap by default)
    NOT normal queue behavior
ЁЯУМ Use when:
    You need sorted processing
    Examples: Dijkstra, Top K problems


ЁЯФ╡ 4. ArrayBlockingQueue (Thread-safe)
Queue<Integer> q = new ArrayBlockingQueue<>(100);
тЬФ Features:
    Fixed size
    Thread-safe (blocking)
ЁЯУМ Use when:
    Producer-consumer problems
    Multithreading

ЁЯФ╡ 5. LinkedBlockingQueue (Thread-safe)
Queue<Integer> q = new LinkedBlockingQueue<>();

ЁЯФ╡ 6. ConcurrentLinkedQueue (Non-blocking)
Queue<Integer> q = new ConcurrentLinkedQueue<>();

ЁЯФ╡ 7. DelayQueue
Queue<Delayed> q = new DelayQueue<>();


Quick Comparison
| Implementation          | Type        | Order  | Thread-safe | Use Case           |
| ----------------------- | ----------- | ------ | ----------- | ------------------ |
| `ArrayDeque` тнР          | Array       | FIFO   | тЭМ           | Best general       |
| `LinkedList`            | Linked list | FIFO   | тЭМ           | Simple use         |
| `PriorityQueue`         | Heap        | Sorted | тЭМ           | Priority problems  |
| `ArrayBlockingQueue`    | Array       | FIFO   | тЬЕ           | Fixed-size threads |
| `LinkedBlockingQueue`   | Linked list | FIFO   | тЬЕ           | Producer-consumer  |
| `ConcurrentLinkedQueue` | Linked list | FIFO   | тЬЕ           | High concurrency   |



тЬЕ Queue + Deque Comparison Table

| Implementation          | Type        | Order  | Thread-safe | Use Case           | Queue Initialization                          | Deque Initialization                |
| ----------------------- | ----------- | ------ | ----------- | ------------------ | --------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------- |
| `ArrayDeque` тнР          | Array       | FIFO   | тЭМ           | Best general       | `Queue<T> q = new ArrayDeque<>();`            | `Deque<T> dq = new ArrayDeque<>();` |
| `LinkedList`            | Linked list | FIFO   | тЭМ           | Simple use         | `Queue<T> q = new LinkedList<>();`            | `Deque<T> dq = new LinkedList<>();` |
| `PriorityQueue`         | Heap        | Sorted | тЭМ           | Priority problems  | `Queue<T> q = new PriorityQueue<>();`         | тЭМ Not supported                     |
| `ArrayBlockingQueue`    | Array       | FIFO   | тЬЕ           | Fixed-size threads | `Queue<T> q = new ArrayBlockingQueue<>(n);`   | тЭМ Not supported                     |
| `LinkedBlockingQueue`   | Linked list | FIFO   | тЬЕ           | Producer-consumer  | `Queue<T> q = new LinkedBlockingQueue<>();`   | тЭМ Not supported                     |
| `ConcurrentLinkedQueue` | Linked list | FIFO   | тЬЕ           | High concurrency   | `Queue<T> q = new ConcurrentLinkedQueue<>();` | тЭМ Not supported                     |
